{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2023-1087","published":"2023-02-17T11:04:54Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:18:23.220831Z","upstream":["CVE-2022-3707","CVE-2023-0615"],"summary":"kernel security update","details":"The Linux Kernel, the operating system core itself.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nA double-free memory flaw was found in the Linux kernel. The Intel GVT-g graphics driver triggers VGA card system resource overload, causing a fail in the intel_gvt_dma_map_guest_page function. This issue could allow a local user to crash the system.(CVE-2022-3707)\r\n\r\nA memory leak flaw and potential divide by zero and Integer overflow was found in the Linux kernel V4L2 and vivid test code functionality. This issue occurs when a user triggers ioctls, such as VIDIOC_S_DV_TIMINGS ioctl. This could allow a local user to crash the system if vivid test code enabled.(CVE-2023-0615)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"kernel","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP3","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/kernel&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["kernel-tools-devel-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","perf-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","python3-perf-debuginfo-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-source-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bpftool-debuginfo-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","perf-debuginfo-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-debuginfo-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","python3-perf-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","python2-perf-debuginfo-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-tools-debuginfo-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","python2-perf-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bpftool-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-debugsource-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-tools-4.19.90-2302.3.0.0188.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kerne